Editor’s note: This live event has ended. You can watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) and the National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) held a joint press briefing on Tuesday to discuss Eskom’s wage offer of 0 percent. The unions had earlier said that workers should not suffer because of plundering at the state-owned entity. The briefing was held at the Garden Court hotel near OR Tambo International Airport. eNCA